    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>High avalanche danger will persist.</highlights>
      <comment>They have received widespread snowfall of 30 to 60 cm of fresh snow, accompanied by strong winds. At higher elevations, the amounts of fresh snow are greater. &lt;br/> The avalanche prone locations are numerous. As a consequence of new snow and wind, deep wind slabs formed. Natural avalanches are further possible. In the regions exposed to heavier precipitation they can in isolated cases reach very large size and in some places endanger transportation routes situated at relatively high altitudes. &lt;br/> Without question, it is inadvisable to engage in backcountry touring.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The new snow and wind slabs are bonding poorly with the old snowpack in all aspects. &lt;br/> Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
    <tendency>
      <highlights>In some regions light snowfall. The wind will be moderate to strong. Significant warming to 2500 m. &lt;br/> The conditions remain dangerous. We recommend that you consult the most recent avalanche bulletin.</highlights>
      <tendencyType>steady</tendencyType>
